Currently [server_main.cc](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/4dc9b5b7ef3049f4fa7c86a99a22bf579a6cbd72/gazebo/server_main.cc#cl-37) uses the return value to determine if a server should be started. If not, it always exits with `return -1;`.

I would interpret the integer as:
~~~
int result = ParseArgs(argc, argv);
// result > 0: start the server
// result <= 0: exit with code result
//  ie. result = 0, will exit successfully
//      result = -1, will exit with a failure code
~~~
